# Vercel Environment Variables Template
# Copy these variables to your Vercel project settings

# ===========================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION
# ===========================================
# Get these from: https://supabase.com/dashboard → Your Project → Settings → API

# Frontend Supabase Configuration (anon key - safe for client-side)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_KEY=your_anon_key_here

# ===========================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ===========================================
# 1. Replace 'your-project-id' with your actual Supabase project ID
# 2. Replace 'your_anon_key_here' with your actual anon/public key
# 3. DO NOT use the service_role key in Vercel (security risk)
# 4. The anon key is safe for frontend use with Row Level Security

# ===========================================
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE
# ===========================================
# 1. Copy the variables above to your Vercel project
# 2. Go to Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add each variable with the correct values
# 4. Set environment to "Production" (and "Preview" if needed)
# 5. Save and redeploy your application

# ===========================================
# GETTING YOUR SUPABASE CREDENTIALS
# ===========================================
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Settings → API
# 4. Copy:
#    - Project URL → use for VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - anon key → use for VITE_SUPABASE_KEY
# 5. DO NOT copy the service_role key (security risk)
